iField_TensorTemplateHandle *  handle,
int *  err

Create a tensor template; return its handle.

Create a tensor template. Once a tensor template is set up, its basic data can be read, but not written. So, for example, if you want to change from a 2-vector to a 3-vector, you need to have another tensor template for that tensor.

Parameters:
instance  [in] iField instance handle
order  Tensor order
num_comp  Number of components
alg_type  [in] Is this data real, complex, etc? (enum)
quant_handle  [in] Physical quantity this tensor represents.
handle  [out] The newly created tensor template.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)
